public String getProperty(String name,
                          String defaultValue)
Gets the value of the specified property. Uses case-insensitive comparison to get the property. Returns the supplied default value if the requested named property does not exist.

Parameters:
name - name of the property, may not be null or empty.
defaultValue - Returned if the property does not exist in the list, may be null or empty.
Returns:
the property value, may be null or empty depending on whether the named property exists and the default value supplied.

setProperty

public void setProperty(String name,

Sets the specified property with supplied value. If the property with that name exists it will be replaced. The property name is compared case-insensitive.

Parameters:
name - name of the property, may not be null or empty.
value - value of the property, may be null or empty. If null supplied, "" is stored.

removeProperty

public boolean removeProperty(String name)
